<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 22 at 8:52AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Spotty light snow and or freezing drizzle is possible through
the morning hours....
A warm front moving through the region may bring isolated areas
of light snow and or freezing drizzle to portions of Blaine county
through the morning hours.
Any accumulations are expected to be negligible, but temperatures
in the teens may allow even trace amounts of precipitation to
freeze on contact.
Use caution if traveling along US highway 2 or other roadways in
Blaine county and be prepared for the possibility of slippery
spots, especially on bridges. Also, be aware that sidewalk
surfaces may become slippery as well.</description>
